==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stellionate
<hw>Stel"lion*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stellionatus</ets> cozenage, trickery, fr. <ets>stellio</ets> a
newt, a crafty, knavish person.]</ety> <fld>(Scots & Roman Law)</fld>
<def>Any fraud not distinguished by a more special name; -- chiefly
applied to sales of the same property to two different persons, or
selling that for one's own which belongs to another, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Erskine.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stellular</ent>⟦br⟧
